o, Sal, Vita.","Italian: from the personal name <i>Ruf(f)ino</i>, from Latin <i>Rufinus</i>, a development of <i>Rufus</i> (see   Ruffo  )."]},{"name":"Ruffin","meanings":["English and French: from the Old French personal name <i>Ruffin</i>, from Latin <i>Rufinus</i>, a diminutive of <i>Rufus</i> ‘red’, borne by several early Christian saints, including a 3rd-century martyr of Soissons and a 4th-century Church Father. Compare   Ruffo  .","English: nickname from Middle English <i>ruffine</i> (Old French <i>rufin</i>) ‘reddish’, for someone with red hair or a ruddy complexion.","English: possibly also a nickname from Middle English <i>ruffin</i> ‘fiend, devil’."]},{"name":"La Ruffa","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Cesare, Eduardo, Italia, Silvio.","Italian (also <b>Laruffa</b>): probably a nickname for someone from a family with red hair (see   Ruffo  )."]},{"name":"Rufo","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Antonio, Mario, Gino, Nino, Pompeo, Rogelio, Romeo, Aldo, Alfonse, Antonino, Benigno, Carmella, Dino, Donato, Emilio, Fortunato, Franco, Giulio, Isidra, Julio, Lauro, Liliana, Onofre.","Italian: variant of   Ruffo  ."]},{"name":"Ruffolo","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Luigi, Aldo, Emilio, Fiorino, Mario, Natale, Serafino, Antonio, Aurelio, Carmine, Duilio, Enrico, Erminio, Ernesto, Filomena, Gaspare, Lilia, Rodolfo, Rosario, Sergio.","Italian (Calabria): from a pet form of the personal name   Ruffo  ."]}]},{"name":"Agnese","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Greek.  See  <b>Agnes</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Agnes","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnese RUFFO was born about 1154, in Italy. She had at least 2 sons with Giordano Ier RUFFO di SINOPOLI. She died in Sinopoli, Reggio Calabria, Calabria, Italy."},"et":{"Abt 1154–":"umbes 1154–Surnud","1152–Male":"1152–Surnud","1170–1243":"1170–1243","–Male":"Surnud","1154–Female":"1154–Surnud","Abt 1154":"umbes 1154","1243":"1243","1154":"1154","1152":"1152","1170":"1170",", , , Italia":"Itaalia","Comune di Sinopoli, Città metropolitana di Reggio Calabria, Calabria, Italia":"Sinopoli, Reggio Calabria, Calabria, Itaalia"},"fi":{"Abt 1154–":"noin 1154–Kuollut","1152–Male":"1152–Kuollut","1170–1243":"1170–1243","–Male":"Kuollut","1154–Female":"1154–Kuollut","Abt 1154":"noin 1154","1243":"1243","1154":"1154","1152":"1152","1170":"1170",", , , Italia":"Italia","Comune di Sinopoli, Città metropolitana di Reggio Calabria, Calabria, Italia":"Sinopoli, Reggio Calabria, Calabria, Italia"},"fr":{"Abt 1154–":"environ 1154–Décédée","1152–Male":"1152–Décédé","1170–1243":"1170–1243","–Male":"Décédé","1154–Female":"1154–Décédée","Abt 1154":"environ 1154","1243":"1243","1154":"1154","1152":"1152","1170":"1170",", , , Italia":"Italie","Comune di Sinopoli, Città metropolitana di Reggio Calabria, Calabria, Italia":"Sinopoli, Reggio Calabria, Calabria, Italie","lifeSummary":"Agnese RUFFO est née environ 1154, à Italie. Elle a eu au moins 2 fils avec Giordano Ier RUFFO di SINOPOLI. Elle est décédée à Sinopoli, Reggio Calabria, Calabria, Italie."},"de":{"Abt 1154–":"um 1154–Verstorben","1152–Male":"1152–Verstorben","1170–1243":"1170–1243","–Male":"Verstorbe